ShareOverviewSummaryPerma-Fix Environmental Services, Inc. and its subsidiaries have worked on two hundred and sixty-nine contracts worth $29.9 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2016), the organization received a total of $2.37 million USD in obligations.The principal agencies it has contracted with are the Department of Veterans Affairs, Department of Defense, and Department of Energy.

